= Objects

Objects are special macros that create interactive and media elements in your documents.

== Overview

Objects extend the functionality of Remarkd by providing macros for links, images, videos, and other special content types. They can be used inline or as block elements.

== Object Types

This category includes the following object types:

* *Links* - Hyperlinks to external URLs and internal references
* *Images* - Image display with various attributes
* *Videos* - Video embedding with poster images
* *Anchors* - Anchor points for internal linking
* *References* - Cross-references to document sections
* *Progress Meters* - Progress indicators and meters
* *Line Breaks* - Explicit line breaks in text

== Usage

Objects use specific syntax patterns and can accept various attributes for customization. Click on any feature above to see examples and learn how to use them in your documents.


